    "created_at": "2011-11-23T00:51:47Z",
    "updated_at": "2011-11-23T00:51:47Z",
    "body": "purity and unsafety are not orthogonal.  At first I thought they ought to be but it made a lot of things harder and I couldn't think of a good reason to support it.  So functions are either normal, pure, or unsafe.  As a side effect, an unsafe block is like an unchecked block but stronger.  I am not sure this is how it _should_ be, but it's not an accident per se.\n",
